** Help support ambulance services to save and improve lives. **

Corvanta is more than a software and technology company. Join a team that
empowers out-of-hospital care providers with timely, integrated, patient-
centric solutions. You’ll see how your work makes a difference in people's
lives and we'll hopefully make a difference in yours.

##  ** About the Role **

You’ll join the team as a ** Cloud Engineer ** to provide Level 1/2 cloud
support, focusing on deployment, maintenance, and issue resolution for our
customers in the Emergency Services industry.

** You’ll have the opportunity to: **

  * Provide primary support for AWS environments, proactively identifying and troubleshooting issues, ensuring the continuous functionality and optimization of AWS infrastructure. 
  * Oversee Windows environments, including effective server management for optimal performance and reliability. 
  * Conduct regular patching activities to ensure systems are up to date with the latest security and performance updates. 
  * Maintain comprehensive documentation of environment configurations, issue resolutions, and best practices. 
  * Continuously assess and optimize AWS infrastructure for performance, scalability, and cost-effectiveness. 
  * Perform limited hardware maintenance to address any critical issues and maintain system integrity. 
  * Work with external cloud partners to improve the overall quality of cloud services. 

** What you’ll bring to the role: **

  * Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, IT, or equivalent. 
  * Experience supporting AWS environments as part of a Level 1/2 service desk or managed service. 
  * Experience with infrastructure as code in AWS environments. 
  * Familiarity with Windows environments, including server management, patching, and basic hardware maintenance. 
  * Familiarity with security tools and practices for cloud environments. 
  * Experience with version control systems such as Git for managing infrastructure changes. 
  * Proactive attitude and adaptability, especially in handling diverse tasks beyond AWS, reflecting the changing nature of the role. 
  * AWS certification; ideally including Cloud Practitioner. 

##  ** Why Corvanta? **

With a team who are truly dedicated and passionate about what they do,
Corvanta understands the impact ambulance services providers have on people’s
lives. In an industry where providing essential health services and excellent
care is paramount, it is crucial patients receive the right care, at the right
time, at the right place. To meet these objectives, our business is solely
focused on delivering quality solutions that support incident response to
influence better outcomes.

We’ll continuously support and develop you so that you can bring your best
self to our team. It’s your ideas, energy, and drive that will help all of us
grow, innovate, and be successful. If you join Corvanta, you will have the
opportunity to:

  * make a difference 
  * join a supportive culture 
  * work locally and globally 
  * invest in continuous learning and developing 
  * have workplace flexibility 
  * access various employee benefit schemes 
  * be challenged every day, and 
  * most importantly, have fun whilst achieving it all! 

Corvanta is part of Modaxo, which brings together 22 brands that solely focus
on People Transportation technology. Corvanta and Modaxo are part of the
Constellation Software Group which is the largest IT company in Canada and has
over 125,000 customers in more than 100 countries across the globe, with
offices on every continent.

** Please note: ** Only applicants with Australian working rights will be considered for this role. You will need to successfully pass an Australian National Police Check if you are successful. 

